Sauer & Sohn Mauser S/147 1937.  A true RC in unmolested form.  I say unmolested because the elements of the Russian rebuild are still evident and have not been altered to remove the historical importance of this rifle's journey from German to Russian heritage.  Typical elements of the Russian "adoption" are intact - "X" marked receiver, period appropriate "re-bluing", bolt force matched via electric pencil, orginal Geman cartouches sanded off from stock and then stock stamped with receiver number, period appropriate red shellac stock.  Receiver bears many Weimer/Reichsadler eagles,  It would be my hope that this rifle is purchsed and kept in its current form.  Experienced firearms collectors know that those surplus arms that are kept in their original surplus form (and not stripped, sanded, altered, etc.) are the firearms that most likely increase in value.  Erasing the Russina heritage of this rifle would be a travesty - the age old saying holds true - " if this rifle could talk".As any collector would expect, additional images are available upon request.  The listed price is the minimum I will accept - if I get several offers, the hightest will get the chance to own this peice of history.  FTF transfers only.
